Arab Potash First-Half Profits Rise 82% to 128.7 Million Dinars

-- B y   M o h a m m a d   T a y s e e r
-- 
2011-08-01T14:55:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-01/arab-potash-first-half-profits-rise-82-to-128-7-million-dinars.html
Arab Potash Co. (APOT)  said its net profit
rose 83 percent to 128.7 million dinars ($181.7 million) in the
first half of 2011, compared with 70.2 million dinars during the
same period last year.  Revenue increased 17 percent in the period to 308.8 million
dinars from 257.3 million dinars during the same period last
year, it said in a filing posted on the website of the  Amman
Stock Exchange .  Among APCâ€™s shareholders are the Potash Corp. of
Saskatchewan,  Canada , which has a 27.96 percent stake, and the
government of Jordan, which holds 26.88 percent of APC.  To contact the reporters on this story:
